# Commit suggestion (mandatory)

At the **end of every response** where you created, modified, or deleted project files, include a **Suggested commit** section in English.

Skip only for pure Q&A with no file changes.

## Format

```markdown
## Suggested commit

**Branch:** `<type>/<short-description>`

\`\`\`bash
git add <paths-or-.>
git commit -m "$(cat <<'EOF'
<type>(<scope>): <imperative subject ≤72 chars>

<optional body — why, not what>
EOF
)"
\`\`\`
```

## Rules

- Follow [docs/contributing/commits.md](../../docs/contributing/commits.md) and [docs/contributing/branches.md](../../docs/contributing/branches.md)
- **English only** — subject imperative mood, ≤ 72 characters
- **Branch** must match topic branch convention (`feat/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, `chore/`, etc.) — never `main`
- **Type** must match change: `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `chore`, `test`, `refactor`, `ci`, `build`
- **Scope** = affected area (`domain`, `api`, `web`, `worker`, `database`, `docs`, `ci`)
- One logical change per commit; list only relevant `git add` paths
- Do not suggest commit if user did not ask and no files were changed

## Examples

**Docs only:**

```text
docs(system): add occurrence lifecycle and privacy principles
```

**Monorepo scaffold:**

```text
build(monorepo): scaffold turborepo with domain package and nestjs api
```

**Feature with body:**

```text
feat(occurrences): add Occurrence aggregate with status transitions

Introduce domain entity and value objects per ADR-0003.
```
